{"detail":{"ID":1237,"post_author":"1","post_date":"2017-04-07 17:45:46","post_date_gmt":"2017-04-07 17:45:46","post_content":"In these times of severe environmental crisis, a <em>City of Science<\/em> is suggestive of something in-between having a perspective of renewed idealism and a resignation to conform to pure market strategies. In view of this epochal urgency, the project proposes to adopt healthier models of life in the interests of safeguarding the planet. Our proposal imagines the largest public park, the largest that the site can accommodate. With landscaping designed by Vogt London, it features a large amount of local and exotic trees. The crescent shaped six-story housing curve follows the trajectory of the sun framing the park to the southeast. It expands the garden of the Flaminia School and gives residents deep green views like from a New York condo on Fifth Avenue or Central Park West. The crescent roof is designed to be both a rainwater collector and a modern aqueduct. Rainwater is released into a tub, a fountain around which the volumes of the <em>City of Science<\/em> are arranged.","post_title":"<p>Citt&agrave; della Scienza, Rome, IT 2015<\/p>","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"citt-della-scienza-masterplan-rome-it-2015","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2017-05-16 16:08:33","post_modified_gmt":"2017-05-16 16:08:33","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":0,"guid":"http:\/\/obra.neptuno.digital\/?post_type=projects&#038;p=1237","menu_order":0,"post_type":"projects","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0","filter":"raw","ancestors":[],"page_template":"","post_category":[],"tags_input":[],"extended":{"year":"","images":[{"image":{"width":1500,"height":927,"file":"2017\/04\/OBRA_CITTA_DELLA_SCIENZA_01.jpg","sizes":{"thumbnail":{"file":"OBRA_CITTA_DELLA_SCIENZA_01-760x460.jpg","width":760,"height":460,"mime-type":"image\/jpeg"},"medium":{"file":"OBRA_C